Ade writes "Looks like the challenge to the Swiss Administrative Court concerning the government contract given to Microsoft without any public bidding was successful: The court has issued a temporary injunction (note: article in German) against the Federal Office of Buildings and Logistics (BBL), effectively stopping the CHF 14M (Â£8M; $15M)-contract to deliver licenses and support for software used on government computers for the next three years.
According to Swiss Government practices, any contract over CHF 50'000 has to undergo a public call for offers.
The BBL cited 'no serious alternatives' as the reason which this contract never did.
